  "prompt": "Can you travel at the speed of light?",
  "response": "According to our current understanding of physics, particularly Einstein's theory of relativity, nothing with mass can travel at the speed of light. As an object with mass approaches the speed of light, its relativistic mass increases, which in turn requires more and more energy to continue accelerating. To reach the speed of light, an infinite amount of energy would be required, which is not feasible.\n\nLight itself, which is composed of massless particles called photons, travels at the speed of light in a vacuum. However, for objects with mass, such as spacecraft or humans, traveling at the speed of light remains impossible within the framework of our current physical laws.",
